# D Transcreate Skill

Use this skill to translate or transcreate long documents with controlled terminology,
consistent voice, and durable state across context windows.

## Canonical Workflow

Read and follow the core entrypoint for operating principles and the full 7-phase workflow:

→ `core/d-transcreate.md`

Phases: Intake → Whole-Document Scan → Research Terminology and Style → Plan Chunks →
Translate in Passes → Coordinate Subagents → Run QA Gates.

## Coordinator Behavior

When orchestrating the translation workflow, adopt the coordinator role defined in:

→ `core/prompts/transcreate-coordinator.md`

The coordinator holds final authority over the global Glossary, Style Sheet, voice
consistency, continuity across chunks, and the merge of all chunk outputs.

